a dependency for meaningful tests, but its JNDI ReferenceableUtils API now requires an ObjectFactory whitelist for overloads that do not take an explicit allowed factory set.\",\n  \"deterministic_setup\": [],\n  \"agent_guidance\": \"When testing com.mchange.v2.naming.ReferenceableUtils.referenceToObject(...), either call an overload that supplies an explicit allowedFactoryClassNames Set containing the test ObjectFactory class name, or set System property com.mchange.v2.naming.objectFactoryWhitelist to that fully-qualified factory class name for the duration of the test and clear it afterward. Avoid enabling remote factory class loading unless a test specifically covers that security behavior.\",\n  \"risks\": [\n    \"Tests copied from older 0.2.15 behavior that call ReferenceableUtils.referenceToObject(reference, name, context, env) without a whitelist will fail on 0.4.0.\",\n    \"Optional integrations such as Typesafe Config, SLF4J, Log4j, or Logback exist in the POM, but they are optional and not required for baseline meaningful coverage.\"\n  ]\n}", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_03e0e2b725ae3cf1016a3ec274ce508196a4e829e34b375294\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 7653, "output": 725, "cacheRead": 26112, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 34490, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "stop", "timestamp": 1782497890553, "responseId": "resp_03e0e2b725ae3cf1016a3ec26300388196b0d31a31cf600cdd"}, "toolResults": []}
